p: Territory of Washington 3rd Judicial District S.S In District Court holding terms at Seattle in King County. In the matter of the application of Author Hain for a writ of Habeas Corpus To L. V. Wyckoff Sheriff of King County in Washington Territory Greeting: We command you, in the name of the United States of America, that you have the body of Author Hain, by you imprisioned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisionment and detention by whatsoever name said Author Hain shall be called or charged before the Hon. J. R. Lewis Chief Justice of Washington Territory and Judge of the 3rd Judicial District therin at his chambers in the city of Seattle on the 5th day of October 1878 at 10 o'clock A. M. of that day to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said Author Hain. And have you then and there this writ. Witness Hon. J. R. Lewis cheif justice of Washington Territory and Judge of said District Court this 4th day of October 1878 James Searey Clerk Lewis Wyckoff Deputy
